= [wiki:AhaWiki] Access Control
== Commands
 * `#!read`
 * `#!write`

== Objects
 * Special
  * `[all]` - all users.
  * `[login]` - users who logged in
 * `specific@e.mail` - `specific@e.mail` user.

== Default Access Control
You can specify default permission at [wiki:.config?action=edit .config]

=== Examples
==== Public Wiki
Anyone can read and write this wiki.
{{{#!Vim hocon
permission {
    default {
        read = "[all]"
        write = "[all]"
    }
}
}}}

==== Open Wiki
Anyone can read, but logged user can write this wiki.
{{{#!Vim hocon
permission {
    default {
        read = "[all]"
        write = "[login]"
    }
}
}}}

==== Closed Wiki
Logged user only
{{{#!Vim hocon
permission {
    default {
        read = "[login]"
        write = "[login]"
    }
}
}}}

==== Private Wiki
Only specified user can use
{{{#!Vim hocon
permission {
    default {
        read = "aha00a@gmail.com,somebody@example.com"
        write = "aha00a@gmail.com"
    }
}
}}}


== Page Level Access Control
You can insert ACL declaration at the top of the specific page.

=== Examples
All users can read, but some users who logged in can edit.
{{{
...
#!read [all]
#!write [login]
= Page Title
Page description
...
}}}

Some users who logged in can see, but only `aha00a` and `aha00b` can edit.
{{{
...
#!read [login]
#!write aha00a,aha00b
= Page Title
Page description
...
}}}

